SIMPLE: specialize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Specialize
<hw>Spe"cial*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
mention specially; to particularize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To apply to some specialty or limited object; to
assign to a specific use; <as>as, <ex>specialized</ex>
knowledge</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>To supply with an organ or organs
having a special function or functions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Specially</ent>⟦br⟧
